1
00:00:11,220 --> 00:00:12,520
Are you all right now?

2
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:19,560
You must be hungry.

3
00:00:21,760 --> 00:00:22,860
Do you want some bread?

4
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:36,510
Tteokbokki.

5
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:41,820
I want to eat tteokbokki.

6
00:00:43,120 --> 00:00:44,120
Okay.

7
00:00:45,190 --> 00:00:46,190
Let's go.

8
00:00:47,860 --> 00:00:48,860
Enjoy.

9
00:00:48,860 --> 00:00:49,860
Thank you.

10
00:00:55,330 --> 00:00:56,360
Help yourself.

11
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,430
- You should eat too.
- What?

12
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:01,100
Gosh.

13
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:03,270
Don't eat it like that. Here.

14
00:01:03,270 --> 00:01:06,210
Gosh. What a good eater.

15
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:08,280
Okay.

16
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:13,580
What is it?

17
00:01:14,180 --> 00:01:16,350
Does it hurt too much to eat?

18
00:01:17,050 --> 00:01:18,050
Well...

19
00:01:19,290 --> 00:01:20,590
No, it's not that.

20
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:27,430
- What is it?
- How can I eat...

21
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:29,930
in front of you when you
can't eat from the injury?

22
00:01:31,030 --> 00:01:32,130
Let's get it packed.

23
00:01:37,940 --> 00:01:39,040
Let's just eat.

24
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:40,540
It doesn't hurt at all.

25
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:51,150
Happy?

26
00:01:51,650 --> 00:01:52,690
Eat up.

27
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,760
How strange.

28
00:01:57,060 --> 00:01:59,930
I thought the world was crumbling...

29
00:01:59,930 --> 00:02:01,830
just a minute ago because of Jin.

30
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:04,330
But for some reason, I can eat well.

31
00:02:09,670 --> 00:02:10,670
Is it good?

32
00:02:11,610 --> 00:02:12,610
Yes.

33
00:02:22,850 --> 00:02:24,820
This is good enough. You should go now.

34
00:02:26,450 --> 00:02:28,460
I'll walk you a little more.

35
00:02:32,790 --> 00:02:34,060
Does it hurt?

36
00:02:34,860 --> 00:02:36,130
Why are you clenching to your side?

37
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,370
- What?
- Did you hurt your ribs?

38
00:02:43,910 --> 00:02:45,770
No, I'm completely fine.

39
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:47,380
Is that so?

40
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,280
(Episode 4)

41
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,350
Hello.

42
00:02:57,550 --> 00:02:58,950
Hey.

43
00:02:59,790 --> 00:03:01,020
Right, Jung Hee.

44
00:03:01,290 --> 00:03:03,190
How's your mom's burn on her hand?

45
00:03:03,230 --> 00:03:05,060
What? My mom?

46
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,490
Don't you know?

47
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:10,000
Your dad came yesterday
and bought bandages.

48
00:03:10,230 --> 00:03:11,530
He did?

49
00:03:12,230 --> 00:03:14,840
Didn't you know your mom was hurt?

50
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:19,840
There's no way Dad would have...

51
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:30,120
Jung Hee, where have you been?

52
00:03:30,350 --> 00:03:31,850
I went for a walk.

53
00:03:31,850 --> 00:03:32,990
Did something happen?

54
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:34,560
No.

55
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,890
Where have you been all night?

56
00:03:37,890 --> 00:03:39,330
Why are you coming home so late?

57
00:03:39,330 --> 00:03:40,800
She was just in front of the house.

58
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,770
Mom, did you burn your hand?

59
00:03:43,770 --> 00:03:45,300
What are you talking about?

60
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:48,040
Did you fall asleep outside?

61
00:03:48,370 --> 00:03:50,010
It's your aunt who got a burn...

62
00:03:50,010 --> 00:03:52,340
after your dad flipped the table.

63
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:55,410
Then why did Dad...

64
00:03:55,580 --> 00:03:58,010
You should go inside and sleep.

65
00:03:58,010 --> 00:04:01,350
I can't seem to stay awake
after I have dinner.

66
00:04:01,350 --> 00:04:02,850
I'm going to bed.

67
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:06,050
Did your dad go out to drink again?

68
00:04:06,050 --> 00:04:07,720
Why isn't he home yet?

69
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:09,930
Ma'am, here you go.

70
00:04:10,890 --> 00:04:12,630
The darn bedpan.

71
00:04:16,230 --> 00:04:17,600
Goodnight.

72
00:04:39,650 --> 00:04:41,390
I went to the book store.

73
00:04:44,430 --> 00:04:45,630
Who is Hae Joo?

74
00:04:50,470 --> 00:04:51,770
Did you go into my room again?

75
00:04:51,770 --> 00:04:54,100
Did your marks drop because of her?

76
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,740
If you don't make it into
Seoul National University,

77
00:04:55,740 --> 00:04:57,310
you'll bring shame to your father.

78
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:59,440
- You know that, right?
- I do.

79
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:06,410
Are you home?

80
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,380
Don't stay out so late.

81
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,650
Things seem to be unstable these days.

82
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,720
- Okay.
- A communist...

83
00:05:14,420 --> 00:05:16,160
somehow got into our mine.

84
00:05:17,030 --> 00:05:18,160
A communist?

85
00:05:18,290 --> 00:05:20,560
I hear he was a professor in Seoul.

86
00:05:24,870 --> 00:05:26,370
What a headache.

87
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,180
Do you think Eng Cho is a beggar?

88
00:05:40,550 --> 00:05:42,550
Did I ask you to do that?

89
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,870
- Hae Joo.
- Dad.

90
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,070
Are you home?

91
00:06:34,540 --> 00:06:35,900
Is Kyung Soo doing well?

92
00:06:39,810 --> 00:06:40,840
Let's go in.

93
00:07:09,570 --> 00:07:10,770
Hey, Lee Jung Hee.

94
00:07:11,610 --> 00:07:13,340
It's not a crime to have a crush.

95
00:07:17,410 --> 00:07:20,420
Be proud. Have confidence.

96
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:31,260
- Jung Hee!
- Hey.

97
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:34,700
Hey, guys.

98
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:38,000
What is this? Are you a Miss Korea?

99
00:07:38,530 --> 00:07:40,800
I heard you went to Gyeryoon High School.

100
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:43,540
My brother told me he saw you.

101
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,070
What?

102
00:07:45,770 --> 00:07:47,610
Did you go there to see Jin?

103
00:07:47,810 --> 00:07:49,740
Don't you have any pride?

104
00:07:49,810 --> 00:07:51,580
Of course I do.

105
00:07:51,850 --> 00:07:54,350
I went yesterday to check on something.

106
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:57,390
I'm over Jin now.

107
00:07:58,150 --> 00:07:59,650
- Are you serious?
- Yes.

108
00:07:59,820 --> 00:08:03,230
I'll be going my way now. Out of my way.

109
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,390
Jung Hee.

110
00:08:08,730 --> 00:08:09,860
Hi, girls.

111
00:08:11,570 --> 00:08:13,840
Hello, Hae Joo.

112
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:19,770
Can we talk?

113
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,540
Sure.

114
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:24,250
Why didn't you tell me?

115
00:08:27,250 --> 00:08:29,220
I saw everything yesterday.

116
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:32,720
I saw Jin waiting at your front door.

117
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,220
I didn't think...

118
00:08:35,420 --> 00:08:37,590
it was necessary to tell you.

119
00:08:37,990 --> 00:08:40,630
There's nothing between Jin and I.

120
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:43,430
I didn't want things to
get awkward between us.

121
00:08:43,830 --> 00:08:45,030
I was scared.

122
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,000
Didn't I tell you?

123
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:50,240
Doing that wouldn't be looking out for me.

124
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:52,210
I was made a fool.

125
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,540
No, Jung Hee. That's not true.

126
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:55,780
That's...

127
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,210
what you think.

128
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:02,620
Anyway, I didn't...

129
00:09:03,420 --> 00:09:04,620
feel so great.

130
00:09:04,890 --> 00:09:05,950
I'm sorry.

131
00:09:07,460 --> 00:09:09,460
It was wrong of me to think that way.

132
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:11,490
I'm sorry, Jung Hee.

133
00:09:15,130 --> 00:09:17,770
I'm completely over...

134
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:19,530
Jin now.

135
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:22,640
I don't have any feelings...

136
00:09:22,970 --> 00:09:24,370
towards Jin...

137
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:29,280
anymore.

138
00:09:31,580 --> 00:09:34,780
You won't have to worry
about my feelings anymore.

139
00:09:36,790 --> 00:09:37,950
That's it.

140
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:42,260
Good job, Jung Hee.

141
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:45,630
You were so brave. You
have your pride back.

142
00:10:05,580 --> 00:10:07,320
What are you doing, Dong Moon?

143
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:09,120
You'll digest all of your lunch.

144
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:11,920
What's with you? Stop that!

145
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:14,990
What's wrong with you? Stop!

146
00:10:26,270 --> 00:10:29,400
- What move is this?
- This?

147
00:10:30,410 --> 00:10:31,740
It's a cream move.

148
00:10:31,740 --> 00:10:34,640
Then this is the streusel move.

149
00:10:39,310 --> 00:10:41,220
Wait, wait.

150
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:45,350
Salute!

151
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:48,590
Salute.

152
00:10:58,430 --> 00:11:01,040
Why would you salute a hypocrite?

153
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:03,670
Don't do that. You dropped my bread!

154
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:06,170
- He's my brother-in-law.
- What?

155
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:08,010
What a joke.

156
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:11,850
Y equals ax squared plus bx plus c.

157
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:14,120
Now, after this...

158
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:15,180
What's wrong with her?

159
00:11:15,350 --> 00:11:16,450
At minus one,

160
00:11:16,450 --> 00:11:19,790
the straight line is approaching x...

161
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:23,560
I'll clench my teeth and study my hardest.

162
00:11:24,030 --> 00:11:26,800
I'll beat Hae Joo.

163
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:44,010
Hae Joo and Gwi Ja can go sit down.

164
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:48,180
Do I still have a long way to catch up?

165
00:11:48,180 --> 00:11:50,420
The rest of you, to your positions.

166
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:52,850
Come on, sir.

167
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:54,390
Positions. Now.

168
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:06,570
You're stupider than pigs.

169
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,940
Look at how Hae Joo solved her question.

170
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,740
Isn't this a work of art?

171
00:12:14,740 --> 00:12:16,550
You eat like everyone else,

172
00:12:16,550 --> 00:12:18,580
and poop like everyone else,

173
00:12:18,580 --> 00:12:19,880
but how are you so different?

174
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:22,450
Jung Hee. Are you ready?

175
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:24,920
Are you ready?

176
00:12:26,050 --> 00:12:28,290
- Yes.
- Okay.

177
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:30,760
Get ready.

178
00:12:31,290 --> 00:12:33,090
Why aren't you getting ready?

179
00:12:33,090 --> 00:12:35,000
- Get ready.
- Get ready.

180
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,000
Mr. Oh!

181
00:12:36,770 --> 00:12:38,530
Yes, Hae Joo?

182
00:12:40,070 --> 00:12:43,310
I'd like you not to give
punishments like that.

183
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:46,270
- What?
- I understand...

184
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:49,680
that you wish to lead us
down the proper path,

185
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:52,210
but using female students' underwear...

186
00:12:52,350 --> 00:12:53,850
will...

187
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:57,550
humiliate the students, in my opinion.

188
00:12:58,290 --> 00:13:00,190
A punishment that humiliates them...

189
00:13:00,190 --> 00:13:02,320
crosses the line from punishment...

190
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,130
to unacceptable assault.

191
00:13:04,890 --> 00:13:05,990
Don't you agree?

192
00:13:10,470 --> 00:13:11,470
What?

193
00:13:12,230 --> 00:13:13,540
Humiliation?

194
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:15,470
Assault?

195
00:13:28,450 --> 00:13:31,890
If that's what you think,
it's understandable.

196
00:13:36,290 --> 00:13:39,430
Fine. I'm consider your point of view.

197
00:13:39,430 --> 00:13:42,360
Hae Joo saved your lives.

198
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,370
Sit down.

199
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:52,010
What are you doing? Sit down.

200
00:13:56,550 --> 00:13:57,650
I didn't know.

201
00:13:57,950 --> 00:14:00,150
I only complained about his punishments...

202
00:14:00,350 --> 00:14:02,080
and accepted it.

203
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:04,790
I only knew how to hold
a grudge and wait...

204
00:14:04,820 --> 00:14:06,390
to get him back someday.

205
00:14:06,620 --> 00:14:09,890
I didn't know I could fight back face on.

206
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:19,100
I'll seriously consider
Hae Joo's comments...

207
00:14:19,130 --> 00:14:22,440
and will not snap your
bra strap as punishment.

208
00:14:26,710 --> 00:14:28,080
Can I...

209
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:30,750
never surpass Hae Joo?

210
00:14:31,180 --> 00:14:33,720
(Military Training)

211
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:49,300
Mr. Oh, is something wrong?

212
00:14:57,740 --> 00:14:59,040
Dang it.

213
00:14:59,470 --> 00:15:02,080
After 10 years of teaching, I, Oh Man Sang,

214
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,810
have to tip toe around a student?

215
00:15:04,350 --> 00:15:05,850
What happened?

216
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:08,180
Did Ae Sook threaten you?

217
00:15:18,190 --> 00:15:19,530
Did she threaten you?

218
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:22,300
We're having an after party this week.

219
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:23,600
An after party?

220
00:15:23,870 --> 00:15:24,870
Yes

221
00:15:25,330 --> 00:15:28,470
We didn't have one after
the broadcast show.

222
00:15:28,970 --> 00:15:30,040
Then...

223
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:32,910
will everyone from Gyeryoon be there?

224
00:15:32,910 --> 00:15:36,380
Yes. I hear Jin is coming too.

225
00:15:47,890 --> 00:15:49,590
(Be a Patriot! Catch Spies!)

226
00:15:49,590 --> 00:15:51,030
No.

227
00:15:51,030 --> 00:15:52,060
Jung Hee.

228
00:15:52,690 --> 00:15:54,260
It's your dad.

229
00:15:56,670 --> 00:15:58,670
- Hello.
- Hello.

230
00:16:04,940 --> 00:16:05,940
Eat.

231
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:08,680
Are you disappointed it isn't ox knee soup?

232
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:11,550
I don't like ox knee soup.

233
00:16:11,580 --> 00:16:12,580
Let's eat.

234
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:19,520
Long time ago,

235
00:16:20,190 --> 00:16:22,890
your youngest aunt drowned.

236
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,490
You never knew, right?

237
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:29,000
You never even saw her face.

238
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,830
I used to carry her everywhere.

239
00:16:32,370 --> 00:16:33,800
But she fell in the river.

240
00:16:35,340 --> 00:16:36,340
Eat.

241
00:16:39,510 --> 00:16:40,710
Here are your vegetables.

242
00:16:41,710 --> 00:16:42,710
Here.

243
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:46,110
Goodness. Young Choon...

244
00:16:47,220 --> 00:16:48,320
Goodbye.

245
00:16:50,520 --> 00:16:51,920
Okay. Bye.

246
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:55,960
Jung Hee.

247
00:16:56,590 --> 00:16:58,930
Don't talk to that guy.

248
00:16:58,930 --> 00:17:00,530
I don't talk to him.

249
00:17:01,230 --> 00:17:02,230
Eat.

250
00:17:11,810 --> 00:17:13,240
Welcome home.

251
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:16,910
- Hi, Jung Hee.
- Why are you back?

252
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,480
Watch how you speak to the teacher.

253
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:19,750
Teacher?

254
00:17:20,550 --> 00:17:23,290
Dong Moon isn't here to see you.

255
00:17:24,190 --> 00:17:26,390
Teacher, please go in.

256
00:17:26,390 --> 00:17:27,390
Sure.

257
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:29,160
You carry this in.

258
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,160
Okay.

259
00:17:33,030 --> 00:17:34,900
- I'll go in now.
- Please, go in.

260
00:17:40,570 --> 00:17:41,770
Tutoring?

261
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:44,240
Dong Moon is Bong Soo's tutor?

262
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,740
Don't tell your father.

263
00:17:45,740 --> 00:17:48,680
I put the money he gave me
for Bong Soo's tutoring...

264
00:17:48,810 --> 00:17:50,150
into a savings group.

265
00:17:50,150 --> 00:17:52,180
Father's so... What about me?

266
00:17:52,180 --> 00:17:54,680
You can sit in and join him.

267
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:58,690
Hey. Dong Moon is the best
in math at the school.

268
00:17:58,690 --> 00:18:00,160
He's nice.

269
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:02,360
I mentioned it in passing,

270
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:04,060
and he said he'd love to.

271
00:18:04,060 --> 00:18:05,560
I don't like him.

272
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:07,000
Then forget it.

273
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,400
I have a lot of work to do.

274
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,800
- I'm leaving.
- What about me?

275
00:18:12,430 --> 00:18:14,040
You can go in there or not.

276
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:16,240
- Do as you wish.
- No. A tutor.

277
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:18,610
Nonsense. I brought a tutor already.

278
00:18:18,610 --> 00:18:20,010
Where are you going?

279
00:18:20,010 --> 00:18:21,080
To the factory!

280
00:18:36,790 --> 00:18:38,760
Darn it.

281
00:18:39,290 --> 00:18:40,460
It's so hard.

282
00:18:40,730 --> 00:18:42,800
I can't even understand the explanation.

283
